title: Casper (1995)
synopsis:
We’ve got a full night of spooky fun planned for you this Halloween, and you won’t want to miss a minute of it! Here’s what’s in store:

5:00 PM: Trick or Treat Scavenger Hunt -
Kick off the evening with a fun scavenger hunt around Semaphore Road! Purchase a ticket to 'Casper (1995)' and grab your goodie bag and map, then visit participating local businesses for cool Halloween treats.

6:30 PM: Casper -
After the scavenger hunt, settle in for a screening of this  family-friendly spooky classic! A perfect Halloween treat for all ages!


CASPER (1995)

An afterlife therapist and his daughter meet a friendly young ghost when they move into a crumbling mansion in order to rid the premises of wicked spirits.

title: Eraserhead (1977)
synopsis: Henry (John Nance) resides alone in a bleak apartment surrounded by industrial gloom. When he discovers that an earlier fling with Mary X (Charlotte Stewart) left her pregnant, he marries the expectant mother and has her move in with him. Things take a decidedly strange turn when the couple's baby turns out to be a bizarre lizard-like creature that won't stop wailing. Other characters, including a disfigured lady who lives inside a radiator, inhabit the building and add to Henry's troubles.

title: Frankenstein
synopsis: Oscar-winning director Guillermo del Toro adapts Mary Shelley’s classic tale of Victor Frankenstein, a brilliant but egotistical scientist who brings a creature to life in a monstrous experiment that ultimately leads to the undoing of both the creator and his tragic creation.

title: Magic at the Movies: Before Sunrise (1995)
synopsis:
'MAGIC AT THE MOVIES' presented by the Odeon Star Cinema. Join us for a curated selection of golden age classics & modern gems! The morning session will feature door prizes, trivia and complimentary morning tea.

BEFORE SUNRISE (1995)

A young man and woman meet on a train in Europe, and wind up spending one evening together in Vienna. Unfortunately, both know that this will probably be their only night together

title: Magic at the Movies: Psycho (1960)
synopsis:
'MAGIC AT THE MOVIES' presented by the Odeon Star Cinema. Join us for a curated selection of golden age classics & modern gems! The morning session will feature door prizes, trivia and complimentary morning tea.

PSYCHO (1960)

A Phoenix secretary steals $40,000 from her employer's client, goes on the run and checks into a remote motel run by a young man under the domination of his mother.

title: Radical Rewind Cinema Club: Back to the Future
synopsis:
Cinemas most celebrated & fun films return to the big screen at the Odeon Star Cinema. Presented by the Radical Rewind Cinema Club!

BACK TO THE FUTURE (1985)
7:00pm - Red Carpet Market
8:00pm - Movie

Marty McFly, a 17-year-old high school student, is accidentally sent 30 years into the past in a time-traveling DeLorean invented by his close friend, the maverick scientist Doc Brown.

title: Regretting You
synopsis: Centers on the strained relationship between young mother Morgan Grant and her teenage daughter Clara, exacerbated by Morgan's husband Chris's tragic death, forcing them to navigate life's challenges together.

title: Springsteen: Deliver Me from Nowhere
synopsis: Bruce Springsteen's journey crafting his 1982 album Nebraska, which emerged as he recorded Born in the USA with the E Street Band. Based on Warren Zanes' book.

title: The Incredibles (2004)
synopsis:
Join us for a special screening of the 2004 smash hit - THE INCREDIBLES!

THE INCREDIBLES follows the adventures of a family of former superheroes rediscovering the true source of their powers – in one another. Once one of the world’s top masked crime fighters, Bob Parr (AKA Mr. Incredible) fought evil and saved lives on a daily basis. But fifteen years later, he and his wife Helen (a famous former superhero in her own right) have been forced to take on civilian identities and retreat to the suburbs.  Today they live as mere mortals and lead alltoo-ordinary lives with their children— who go out of their way to appear “normal.” As a clockpunching insurance man, the only thing Bob fights these days is boredom and a bulging waistline. Itching for action, the sidelined superhero gets his chance when a mysterious communication summons him to a remote island for a top-secret assignment. Now, with the fate of the world hanging in the balance, the family must come together and once again find the fantastic in their family life.

title: The Scientific Bubble Show
synopsis:
Discover the amazing science of bubbles with Bubble-ologist Marty McBubble in this LIVE and IN-PERSON show!

How are bubbles created?  Why do they pop?
What shapes and colours can bubbles make?
Is a bubble a solid, a liquid, or a gas?
What's it like to be inside a bubble?

Children will discover all of this and much more as Marty engages their natural sense of wonder with his interactive, bubbly experiments.

Tickets: $15 / Family Ticket (2 Adults + 2 Children: $50

title: The Travellers
synopsis:
The Travellers is a poignant, funny and heartwarming family story from acclaimed filmmaker Bruce Beresford.
 
Stephen Seary, a charismatic and successful stage designer, returns to his small hometown in Australia to say goodbye to his dying mother.  What was to be a quick trip descends into chaos, drama, and at times downright funny moments as Stephen navigates family responsibilities, a difficult relationship with his father, old friends & past lovers, all while trying to return to Europe for a major opera contract.

title: Windback Wednesday: Poltergeist (1982)
synopsis:
‘WINDBACK WEDNESDAY’ presented by the Odeon Star Cinema. Join us every Wednesday night as we bring cult classics and fan favourites back to the big screen!

POLTERGEIST (1982)

Strange and creepy happenings beset an average California family, the Freelings -- Steve (Craig T. Nelson), Diane (JoBeth Williams), teenaged Dana (Dominique Dunne), eight-year-old Robbie (Oliver Robins), and five-year-old Carol Ann (Heather O'Rourke) -- when ghosts commune with them through the television set. Initially friendly and playful, the spirits turn unexpectedly menacing, and, when Carol Ann goes missing, Steve and Diane turn to a parapsychologist and eventually an exorcist for help.

title: Windback Wednesday: Spider-Man 2 (2004)
synopsis:
‘WINDBACK WEDNESDAY’ presented by the Odeon Star Cinema. Join us every Wednesday night as we bring cult classics and fan favourites back to the big screen!

SPIDER-MAN 2 (2004)

Peter Parker is going through a major identity crisis. Burned out from being Spider-Man, he decides to shelve his superhero alter ego, which leaves the city suffering in the wake of carnage left by the evil Doc Ock. In the meantime, Parker still can't act on his feelings for Mary Jane Watson, a girl he's loved since childhood. A certain anger begins to brew in his best friend Harry Osborn as well...
